common.model

Class AbstractLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • common.model.AbstractType
      • common.model.AbstractLevel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICopy, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AbstractLevel>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EliminationLevel, LightningLevel, PuzzleLevel, ReleaseLevel

    public abstract class AbstractLevel
extends AbstractType
implements java.lang.Comparable<AbstractLevel>, ICopy, java.io.Serializable
    Defines a framework for all Level objects, which can be built and played. Level objects contain information that can be stored on disk and loaded.
    Author:
    Nicholas Panzarino, jasirocki - jdoc
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • squareTypes

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Class<? extends AbstractSquare>> squareTypes()
        Returns an ArrayList containing the classes of allowable squares. These squares will appear in the builder and can be placed anywhere on the board. The default allowable types are: EmptySquares and Squares. A level class which extends this one can change the default by overriding/hiding this method.
        Returns:
        an ArrayList containing the classes of allowable squares

      • getSquareTypes

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Class<? extends AbstractSquare>> getSquareTypes(java.lang.Class<? extends AbstractLevel> c)
        Returns a list of all possible special moves for the input level class. Used to determine the special moves of an unknown level when it is known as a parameter during runtime.
        Parameters:
        c - some class which extends abstract level
        Returns:
        an ArrayList containing the classes of allowable squares

      • moveTypes

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Class<? extends AbstractMove>> moveTypes()
        Returns an ArrayList containing the classes of selectable moves. The default allowable types are: Regular(Add to 6), Reset, Swap, Remove. A level class which extends this one can change the default by overriding/hiding this method.
        Returns:
        an ArrayList containing the classes of selectable moves
